 Jim Marsland Morton came along at tea so we had a yarn : Saturday Oct 28th Ribemont : cold day : met F Pool in morn : he had just come back gave me a photo : wrote in afternoon sent " Alfs " thing the letter that I had written : the mud slush is rotten : everi place is like a pig stye in wet weather : Sunday Oct 29th Ribemont : cold showeri day : up about 7am : Holi Comm at 9.30 am in girl school : it was veri nice with about 40 be present : parad for the lad at 11am : paid 20 franc after dinner : had a walk with Tom watch some german prison work on the road take off the slush : went to church at "Ecole de fill " had a good turn out : there must have been 60 easili there the boy sang well : met Sorrenson had a yarn over old time with him : Monday Oct 30th Ribemont : cold showeri : up about 7am : boy had a parad address by Capt J in morn also in afternoon : I wrote in afternoon also repli to Kati Hubbard note : had a good feed of steak befor turn in : Tuesday Oct 31st Ribemont : showeri day : up about 7 am : boy on parad in morn afternoon : I had a stroll with Jim Hendren had a good laugh over his experi in Amien : veri cold night sent home all the P.C.s that I have so far reciev : Wednesday Nov 1st All Saint Day Ribemont : cold showeri day : up about 6 am
